      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "The avalanche prone locations are to be found in particular at the base of rock walls and adjacent to ridgelines and in gullies and bowls. The avalanches can be released in deep layers of the snowpack. They can in many places be released, even by a single winter sport participant. Shooting cracks when stepping on the snowpack and whumpfing sounds can indicate the danger. Great caution and restraint are required.",
        "highlights": "Considerable avalanche danger will prevail. <br/> As a consequence of new snow and wind the prevalence of the avalanche prone locations will increase as the day progresses."
